The paper deals with secure multi-terminal source coding problems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) communities. The use of a public helper and the consideration of information leakage also suggest a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and security and privacy (cs.SI) subfields. Finally, the paper may also touch upon aspects of communication complexity (cs.CC) due to the triangular source coding scenario.
